---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Quality Assurance | PeptideResearch.eu" description="Our commitment to purity. Learn about our HPLC and Mass Spectrometry testing protocols for research peptides.">
  <section class="page-title bg-2">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
            <ul class="list-inline mb-0">
              <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="/" class="text-sm letter-spacing text-white text-uppercase font-weight-bold">Home</a></li>
              <li class="list-inline-item"><span class="text-white">|</span></li>
              <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" class="text-color text-uppercase text-sm letter-spacing">Quality</a></li>
            </ul>
             <h1 class="text-lg text-white mt-2">Quality Assurance</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
          <p class="lead mb-5">In scientific research, the integrity of your data depends on the integrity of your reagents. We implement a rigorous quality control process to ensure every vial meets the highest standards.</p>

          <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h3 class="card-title">HPLC Analysis</h3>
                  <p class="card-text">High-Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC) is used to determine the purity of the peptide. We guarantee a minimum purity of 98% for all our catalog items. This ensures that impurities, such as deletion sequences or incomplete synthesis byproducts, are minimized.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h3 class="card-title">Mass Spectrometry</h3>
                  <p class="card-text">Mass Spectrometry (MS) is performed to verify the molecular weight and identity of the peptide. This confirms that the amino acid sequence is correct and matches the theoretical mass.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2>Certificate of Analysis (COA)</h2>
          <p>Transparency is key. A Certificate of Analysis is available for every batch we produce. You can download the COA directly from the product page before you buy.</p>
          
          <p><strong>A standard COA includes:</strong></p>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Batch Number</li>
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Date of Analysis</li>
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Theoretical vs. Measured Molecular Weight</li>
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Purity Percentage (HPLC Chromatogram)</li>
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Physical Appearance</li>
            <li><i class="ti-check mr-2 text-color"></i>Solubility Profile</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="mt-5">Storage & Handling</h2>
          <p>To maintain the quality of our peptides after they leave our facility, we recommend the following:</p>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
             <li><i class="ti-angle-right mr-2 text-color"></i>Store lyophilized peptides at -20°C.</li>
             <li><i class="ti-angle-right mr-2 text-color"></i>Keep away from direct sunlight.</li>
             <li><i class="ti-angle-right mr-2 text-color"></i>Minimize freeze-thaw cycles.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
